Durban -  Seven people were injured this morning when a taxi and light motor vehicle collided on the R33 in Copesville, KwaZulu Natal. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said they arrived on scene, along with other emergency services around 6am to find the taxi in the middle of the road while the light motor vehicle had come to a stop on the pavement. "Medics assessed the patients and found that seven people had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate. Fortunately, no serious injuries or fatalities were found,' said Meiring. Patients were taken to hospital. In a seperate incident four people were injured following a collision between two light motor vehicles at the P177 and Umlaas Road in Thornville, KwaZulu Natal. "Medics assessed the patients and found that one person had sustained serious injuries while three others had sustained minor to moderate injuries. The patients were treated for their injuries and thereafter transported to Mediclinic Pietermaritzburg and Edendale Provincial hospital for further care. SAPS  were on scene for both incidents. POST